February 1, 2020  
Appendix C ‚Äì Facility Risk Models 
Example Tools for Gas Facility Risk Assessment79 
Three examples are shown of risk assessment tools used by an operator for facility risk assessment.  
These examples indicate threats and risk factors that should be included in facility risk models. 
Figure C-1 shows an example ‚Äúthreat matrix‚Äù indicating threats and risk factors for a qualitative gas 
system facility risk assessment.  Note that this process includes threats to facility reliability and 
emergency response as well integrity threats.  The figure shows candidate preventive measures for each 
threat. 
Figure C-2 shows an example table of threats and failure causes to be considered in a gas facility risk 
assessment process. 
Figure C-3 shows a portion of a ‚Äúrisk register‚Äù used as a qualitative risk assessment model.  The model 
includes: 
‚Ä¢ Seven frequency levels (the highest 2 are shown), from ‚ÄúCommon‚Äù (>10 times per year), down 
to ‚ÄúRemote‚Äù (once every 100+ years) 
‚Ä¢ Seven impact (consequence) levels (highest 2 shown), from ‚ÄúCatastrophic‚Äù down to ‚ÄúNegligible 
‚Ä¢ Impact levels are defined for six categories (two are shown), including: 
